3.
Margin: controls space outside an element, affecting spacing between elements. Margins can also collapse.
Padding: adjusts space inside an element, influencing spacing between content and the element's border. Padding doesn't collapse.
Border: defines a visible boundary around an element for styling purposes, it's placed just outside the padding.

4.
display: flex:
this turns a container into a flex container for flexible and responsive layout.

flex-direction:
this sets the direction of flexible items (horizontal, vertical, or reversed).

flex-wrap:
this controls item wrapping within a flex container (no wrap, wrap, or reverse wrap).

justify-content/align-items:
this aligns items along the main (horizontal or vertical) and cross (opposite) axes.

align-content:
this aligns multiple lines of items when they wrap within a container.
